{"id":42635,"date":"2024-01-17T23:03:56","date_gmt":"2024-01-17T17:33:56","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/?p=42635"},"modified":"2023-02-17T23:04:00","modified_gmt":"2023-02-17T17:34:00","slug":"small-side-table-designs","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/home-interiors\/small-side-table-designs\/","title":{"rendered":"Sassy Side Kicks: 10 Charming Small Side Table Designs For Your Home"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<p>Small in size, big on style \u2014 take a look at our collection of small side table designs for your home.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Thank God for small mercies! But what about? About those small but essential cogs in the massive wheel that is your home \u2014 the small side tables that carry the weight of knick-knacks of uncertain placement, the small side tables that disguise dubious nooks into captivating corners.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Chosen mostly as an afterthought, rarely do the small side tables receive the exhaustive research that goes into choosing the bed frame or the living room upholstery. And yet, these accent pieces can elevate the room from meh to wow instantly.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Small side tables are more than platforms to park your books and trinkets. They merit more love and attention than just a cursory tick mark on your home furniture list. We make your work easy with our comprehensive list of the trending small <a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/living-room-interiors\/side-table-designs-for-living-room\/\">side table designs<\/a>. You are welcome!<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Mid-Century Modern Small Side Tables<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>We end up with a lot of collected stuff and are unable to display it, so rethinking small side tables as storage options is imperative, especially in apartments. Drawers and lift-top side tables will declutter any room. For a mid-century modern aesthetic, choose small side tables with curved or straight legs, pastel colours and functional drawers.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/02\/17223705\/modern-small-side-tables-in-mid-century-style.jpg\" alt=\"Modern small side tables in mid-century style\" class=\"wp-image-42645\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/02\/17223705\/modern-small-side-tables-in-mid-century-style.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/02\/17223705\/modern-small-side-tables-in-mid-century-style-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/02\/17223705\/modern-small-side-tables-in-mid-century-style-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/02\/17223705\/modern-small-side-tables-in-mid-century-style-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption>Mid-century modern side tables for a pretty home<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Industrial-Style Small Side Tables<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Simple metal legs that balance out the density of the furniture nearby make great additions to industrial-themed home decor. If you can find a multi-tiered side table, it will help you create different visual focal points.\u00a0<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/02\/17223700\/small-side-tables-in-industrial-style.jpg\" alt=\"Small side tables in industrial-style\" class=\"wp-image-42644\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/02\/17223700\/small-side-tables-in-industrial-style.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/02\/17223700\/small-side-tables-in-industrial-style-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/02\/17223700\/small-side-tables-in-industrial-style-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/02\/17223700\/small-side-tables-in-industrial-style-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption>Industrial side tables to declutter surroundings<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Contemporary Small Side Tables<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>These small side tables for the bedroom will look graceful in the living room equally well. White or light-coloured wooden side tables are the most popular choices, but a palette of other shades also looks gorgeous when placed with complementary <a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/living-room-interiors\/living-room-accessories\/\">decor pieces<\/a>.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/02\/17223655\/small-side-tables-in-contemporary-style.jpg\" alt=\"Small side tables in contemporary style\" class=\"wp-image-42643\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/02\/17223655\/small-side-tables-in-contemporary-style.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/02\/17223655\/small-side-tables-in-contemporary-style-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/02\/17223655\/small-side-tables-in-contemporary-style-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/02\/17223655\/small-side-tables-in-contemporary-style-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption>Small side tables that amp up the glam quotient<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Rustic Small Side Tables<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Blonde wood table tops of these small side tables string the aesthetics of the <a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/home-decor\/rustic-home-decor-ideas\/\">rustic home decor<\/a> and create a harmony of colour, mood and the typical earthy vibe of this trend. Make the tablescape more interesting by placing plants, beaten brass pots or ceramic figurines.\u00a0<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/02\/17223649\/small-side-tables-in-rustic-touch.jpg\" alt=\"Small side tables in rustic touch\" class=\"wp-image-42642\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/02\/17223649\/small-side-tables-in-rustic-touch.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/02\/17223649\/small-side-tables-in-rustic-touch-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/02\/17223649\/small-side-tables-in-rustic-touch-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/02\/17223649\/small-side-tables-in-rustic-touch-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption>Rustic small side table can dazzle any corner<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"mbgc-slide-caption\"><a href=\"#contactUsModal\" data-toggle=\"modal\"><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"img-fluid\" alt=\"Space saving home interiors with 20% extra space\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/12\/26112643\/space-saving-home-interiors-with-20-extra-space-scaled.jpg \" \/><\/a><\/div>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Small Side Tables For Masculine Spaces<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Wondering how to dress your man cave? Confused about how to style the side tables in your bachelor pad? Using small side tables with wire legs \u2014 they look great in gold and black or the regular wooden frame will both fit well in more masculine surroundings.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/02\/17223644\/small-side-tables-for-masculine-spaces.jpg\" alt=\"Small side tables for masculine spaces\" class=\"wp-image-42641\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/02\/17223644\/small-side-tables-for-masculine-spaces.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/02\/17223644\/small-side-tables-for-masculine-spaces-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/02\/17223644\/small-side-tables-for-masculine-spaces-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/02\/17223644\/small-side-tables-for-masculine-spaces-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption>These small side tables mean business<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Vintage Small Side Tables<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Vintage style is all about curves, soft furnishings and plush seating. The ornate furniture and heavy drapes characteristic of vintage decor can be balanced beautifully by light, small wood side tables. You could experiment with modern or mid-century-styled small side tables to add a breath of fresh air.\u00a0<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/02\/17223638\/small-side-tables-in-vintage-style.jpg\" alt=\"Small side tables in vintage style\" class=\"wp-image-42640\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/02\/17223638\/small-side-tables-in-vintage-style.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/02\/17223638\/small-side-tables-in-vintage-style-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/02\/17223638\/small-side-tables-in-vintage-style-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/02\/17223638\/small-side-tables-in-vintage-style-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption>Vintage rooms can benefit from small side tables<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Floating Small Side Tables<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Not every small side table needs legs. To save floor space and use the under-table area, you can think of going vertical with floating or built-in small side tables. Hanging a shelf from the ceiling with ropes can be an exciting alternative to a small side table for the bedroom.\u00a0<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/02\/17223634\/floating-small-side-tables-to-save-floor-space.jpg\" alt=\"Floating Small Side Tables to save floor space\" class=\"wp-image-42639\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/02\/17223634\/floating-small-side-tables-to-save-floor-space.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/02\/17223634\/floating-small-side-tables-to-save-floor-space-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/02\/17223634\/floating-small-side-tables-to-save-floor-space-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/02\/17223634\/floating-small-side-tables-to-save-floor-space-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption>Floating side tables are trending this season<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Quirky Small Side Tables<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Walk away from the beaten path with small side tables for the living room or bedroom in unique and unconventional shapes and styles. Quirky is in with many stores offering fascinating designs to complement your experimental personality.\u00a0<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/02\/17223628\/quirky-small-side-tables.jpg\" alt=\"quirky small side tables to complement your personality\" class=\"wp-image-42638\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/02\/17223628\/quirky-small-side-tables.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/02\/17223628\/quirky-small-side-tables-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/02\/17223628\/quirky-small-side-tables-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/02\/17223628\/quirky-small-side-tables-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption>A small side table that\u2019s a work of art<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Small Side Tables For The Kids&#8217; Room<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>No other place needs side tables more than the kids&#8217; room with their books, toys, night lamps and other knick-knacks. Since their rooms are smaller, small side tables are best suited. Built-in side tables in the bed frame open up the floor to store more things in baskets and colourful boxes.\u00a0<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/02\/17223622\/small-side-tables-for-the-kids-room.jpg\" alt=\"small side tables for the kids room\" class=\"wp-image-42637\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/02\/17223622\/small-side-tables-for-the-kids-room.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/02\/17223622\/small-side-tables-for-the-kids-room-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/02\/17223622\/small-side-tables-for-the-kids-room-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/02\/17223622\/small-side-tables-for-the-kids-room-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption>Small side tables are most useful in kids&#8217; rooms<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"mbgc-slide-caption\"><a href=\"#contactUsModal\" data-toggle=\"modal\"><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"img-fluid\" alt=\"Give your home a luxe look with modular home interiors\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/12\/26112428\/give-your-home-a-luxe-look-with-modular-home-interiors-scaled.jpg \" \/><\/a><\/div>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Low Small Side Tables<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Instead of the regular height, you could experiment with low small side tables. These draw attention to the lower regions of the room and add a charming element visually. Low small side tables work best in bedrooms with lower-placed beds. They may not be suitable for the living room unless you have low seating there.\u00a0<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/02\/17223615\/low-small-side-tables.jpg\" alt=\"low small side tables\" class=\"wp-image-42636\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/02\/17223615\/low-small-side-tables.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/02\/17223615\/low-small-side-tables-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/02\/17223615\/low-small-side-tables-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/02\/17223615\/low-small-side-tables-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption>Go low with these small side tables<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Small side tables for the bedroom or the living room have come a long way from yesteryears. New trends hit this segment every year and keep our bedside and living room corners exciting. Don&#8217;t be fooled by their size \u2014 all great things come in small sizes.<\/p>\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<div class=\"row blog-form\">\n\t<div class=\"offset-lg-3 col-lg-6 bg-light\">\n<fieldset class=\"field-set\">\n<!-- <legend align=\"left\"> -->\n 